                            <comment id="15004717" author="eclark" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2015 21:06:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is critical at least.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15004723" author="mbertozzi" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2015 21:09:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;isn&apos;t this &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14777&quot; title=&quot;Fix Inter Cluster Replication Future ordering issues&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-14777&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-14777&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15004785" author="ashu210890" created="Fri, 13 Nov 2015 22:01:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt; On second thoughts, I see that it is not just the retry logic that is broken, but this will cause the HBaseInterClusterReplicationEndpoint.replicate to fail every single time because the IndexOutOfBoundsException is not handled in there. The ReplicationSource keeps sending the same batch again and again, and the replication is completely stuck. This might make it a blocker, rather than just critical.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mbertozzi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mbertozzi&quot;&gt;Matteo Bertozzi&lt;/a&gt; Looks like it is. Thanks for pointing it out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
